6 \x01 \x07 \x08 consumed P (Brightness) \x0e e.g.', 'If 100 W, 220 V bulb operates on 110 volt supply then 2 consumed 110 P 100 25W 220 \x05 \x06 \x01 \x18 \x01 \x07 \x08 If VA < VR then % drop in output power R consumed R (P P ) 100 P \x03 \x01 \x18 For the series combination of bulbs, current through them will be same so they will consume power in the ratio of resistance i.e., P \x0e R {By P = i2R) while if they are connected in parallel i.e.', 'V is constant so power consumed by them is in the reverse ratio of their resistance i.e.', '1 P R \x0e (5) Thickness of filament of bulb : We know that resistance of filament of bulb is given by 2 R R V R , P \x01 also R , A \x01 \x17 l hence we can say that R Thickness 1 A P R \x0e \x0e i.e.', 'If rated power of a bulb is more, thickness of it’s filament is also more and it’s resistance will be less.', 'JEE | NEET | Class 8 - 10 Download eSaral App www.esaral.com Rev.', 'Notes Class 12 Physics Chapter-2'], 'model': 'text-embedding-3-small', 'encoding_format': 'base64'}}
