e to deflect this coherent or co-operative cloud of electrons in super-conductors. It means the coherent cloud of electrons makes no collisions with ions of the super-conductor and, as such, there is no resistance offered by the super-conductor to the flow of electrons.\n\n[Source: electricity.pdf | Page: 16 | Chunk: 153]\nTheir negative terminals are connected to two terminals 1 and 2 of two ways key, while its common terminal 3 is connected to jockey J through a galvanometer G.\n\nQuestion: list all the formulas in the electricity pdf'}], 'model': 'gpt-4.1', 'temperature': 0.2}}
